(firstQuint)Efficacy and Safety of Iloperidone Compared With Placebo and Active Control in Subjects With Acute Schizophrenia.

 Schizophrenia is a severe mental illness affecting an estimated 1% of the world's population.

 Patients with schizophrenia suffer from productive symptoms (e.

g.

, hallucinations and delusions), and deficit symptoms (e.

g.

, a reduction or absence of normal behaviors or emotions).

 Other symptoms include a reduced ability to recall and learn new information.

 Iloperidone is being development as a treatment for symptoms of schizophrenia.

 This trial will test the safety and efficacy of iloperidone in patients with an acute exacerbation of the disease.

